Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of determining the asymptotic algebraic complexity of matrix multiplication, which is a central problem in algebraic complexity theory. The paper introduces a new and more general barrier, providing stronger limitations than in previous work, and introduces the notion of "irreversibility" of a tensor. The paper discusses barriers on the group-theoretic approach in terms of "monomial" irreversibility. Based on this, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
